cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.SI, cs.DC 

This paper focuses on the security and performance aspects of DNS-over-HTTPS (DoH), which falls under the categories of computer security (cs.CR), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), software engineering (cs.SE), social and information networks (cs.SI), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper discusses the compliance and features of public DoH servers, compares different secure DNS transports, and quantifies the overhead incurred by the additional layers of the DoH transport.
